hor_association":"NONE","body":"for reference, a solution seems to be here:\r\n\r\nhttp:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/questions\/35283320\/three-js-rotate-camera-with-both-touch-and-device-orientation\r\n","created_at":"2017-05-01T15:12:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9047#issuecomment-298351584","id":298351584,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9047","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5ODM1MTU4NA==","updated_at":"2017-05-01T15:12:59.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/298351584","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/10294095?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/morandd","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMjk0MDk1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"morandd","type":"User","id":10294095,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/morandd\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I've been struggling with this for days. I've got a 98% solid solution.\r\n\r\nOn drag, I update lon and lat:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction onMouseMove( event ) {\r\n\tlon = ( event.clientX - onPointerDownPointerX ) * dragSpeed + onPointerDownLon;\r\n\tlat = ( event.clientY - onPointerDownPointerY ) * dragSpeed + onPointerDownLat;\r\n}\r\n```\r\nIn my animate function, I assign lon\/lat to alphaOffset and betaOffset.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction animate(time) {\r\n\t\trequestAnimationFrame( animate );\r\n\t\t\r\n\t\tif (!gyroPresent && !manualMove)\tlon += .15;\r\n\t\tlat = Math.max( - 85, Math.min( 85, lat ) );\r\n\t\tcontrols['alphaOffset'] = lon;\r\n\t\tcontrols['betaOffset'] = lat;\r\n\t\tcontrols.update();\r\n\t\trenderer.render( scene, camera );\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThen in DeviceOrientationControls, I offset the data from the device with those numbers.\r\n```\r\n\tthis.update = function () {\r\n\t\tif ( scope.enabled === false ) return;\r\n\t\tif ( !scope.deviceOrientation ) {\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\tscope.deviceOrientation = {alpha:90, beta:90, gamma:0};\r\n\t\t\tscope.screenOrientation = 0;\r\n\t\t}\r\n\r\n\t\tvar device = scope.deviceOrientation;\r\n\t\tvar alpha = THREE.Math.degToRad( device.alpha + scope.alphaOffset ); \/\/ Z\r\n\t\tvar beta = THREE.Math.degToRad( device.beta + scope.betaOffset ); \/\/ X'\r\n\t\tvar gamma = THREE.Math.degToRad( device.gamma + scope.gammaOffset ); \/\/ Y''\r\n\t\tvar orient = THREE.Math.degToRad( scope.screenOrientation ); \/\/ O\r\n\r\n\t\tsetObjectQuaternion( scope.object.quaternion, alpha, beta, gamma, orient );\r\n\t};\r\n\r\n```","created_at":"2018-10-23T15:19:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9047#issuecomment-432291690","id":432291690,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9047","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMjI5MTY5MA==","updated_at":"2018-10-23T15:19:59.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/432291690","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/18600550?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/jtreat3","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NjAwNTUw","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"jtreat3","type":"User","id":18600550,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jtreat3\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@jtreat3 do you have a complete example? Thx!","created_at":"2018-10-24T15:42:11.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9047#issuecomment-432711692","id":432711692,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/9047","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQzMjcxMTY5Mg==","updated_at":"2018-10-24T15:42:11.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/432711692","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/379706?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mattrei","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM3OTcwNg==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mattrei","type":"User","id":379706,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mattrei\/or